According to Steffen Haeuser Quake II is nearly finished.{p}
The game is in its final stage and its in the hands of beta testers to iron out the final bugs.{p}
If you want to know more about it there is a preview of Quake 2 available in a previous issue of AIO.{p}
Knowing Hyperion and Steffen Haeuser I am sure Quake 2 is going to be a massive conversion.{p}
Let's hope it will be released soon.{p}
Keep an eye on AIO for a future review
{pp}
{pp}
Do you remember Rokets, the space_shot'em_up_racer?{p}
The game is an amazing exeprience, especially in two player mode, and it has now reached version 1.39 and become freeware.{p}
Check the review in this very issue of AIO.{p}
{pp}
{pp}
Nobody has heard anything about it. Yet, according to the publisher it is coming very soon.{p}
The Tycoon series is one of the most famous and succesful on PC where gamers have had the opportunity to create and run car companies, malls, golf resources and, just recently, a zoo.{p}
Now Amiga gamers can finally have a go at one of the series called Software Tycoon.{p}
If you are into games and your dream has always been the one to create a new videogame then get ready because Software Tycoon will give you a chance to create and run a big software house taking care of the game concept, hiring staff, deciding the packaging, design, marketing campaigns and much, much more.{p}
