{pp}
For the past few weeks there were rumours going around about a new game from ClickBOOM.{p}
Finally they have announced not one but five new games for Amiga.{p}
Details are not clear but I guess some of them must be re-makes of the various Cinemaware titles. In fact ClickBOOM has been recently very busy  in coding digital remastered versions of the famous Defender Of The Crown, The three Stooges, etc. for PC and MAC and I am sure they would not want to waste their code without porting it on to the Amiga.
{pp}
They are also still working on the strategic game Z, which I hope will come out soon before it becomes too old to match today standards.
{pp}
A sequel for Napalm is in the pipeline. The games was very succesful at the time it came out and a sequel was always in ClickBOOM original plans.
{pp}
For all the people who have had to put up with a defective Nightlong cd ClickBOOM has finally made avaIable Nightlong CD V1.1 which should fix all the original problems.
{pp}
But the reale news is the development of a new game called 666.{p}
Details are scarce but the press release confirmed that it is going to be a demonic 3D action adventure with many twists.{p}
